The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared President Muhammadu Buhari as the winner of this year’s election for a second term. Chairman of the commission who is also the Chief Returning officer of the elections, Prof. Mahmood Yakubu said the APC polled 15,191,847 to defeat the PDPs Atiku Abubakar who garnered 11,262,978 votes. Yakubu said the Certificate of Return would be issued to President Buhari and his running mate, Vice President Yemi Osinbajo today by 2:00pm. Buhari leads Atiku with 1,004, 011 votes from 18 states PDP rejects results as Buhari maintains lead Buhari, APC using state resources, apparatus in violation of electoral laws – Atiku